==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|bewteful}}, {{m|enm|beautefull||attractive to the eye, beautiful}}, equivalent to {{suffix|beauty|ful|lang=en}}. Displaced earlier {{m|en|sheen}} (from {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|schene||beautiful}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|scīene||beautiful}}), {{etyl|enm|-}} {{m|enm|wliti||beautiful}}, from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{m|ang|wlitiġ||beautiful}}.

